Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Wrap each @British Chicken Breasts{2} with 2 rashers of @British Streaky Bacon{4%rashers}.

Pop onto a #baking tray{}. Roast on the middle shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands after handling raw meat and its packaging. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, remove the outer sleeve and plastic film from the top of the @Cauliflower Cheese{350%grams}.

Place on another baking tray. Bake on the top shelf, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven.

Drizzle over the @Hot Sauce{50%grams} and @Honey{15%grams}. Turn to coat.

> TIP: Pop hardened honey into hot water for 1 min.

Transfer the chicken to your plates with any remaining sauce from the tray.

Serve the cauli cheese on the side.

Add the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} and @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%grams} to your plates. Drizzle over the @French Dressing{30%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!